text: James Moore (August 30, 1890 - October 28, 1971) was an American fencer. He competed in the individual épée event at the 1912 Summer Olympics. He graduated from Harvard University and Harvard Law School. ==References== Category:1890 births Category:1971 deaths Category:American male fencers Category:Olympic fencers of the United States Category:Fencers at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Detroit Category:Harvard Crimson fencers Category:Harvard Law School alumni
